  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "When replacing kube-dns v11 (as defined w/ the v1.2.4 release) with v15 in the v1.3.0 release, we notice that the `skydns` container inside the `kube-dns` pod is overly verbose. This appears to be due to an inability to turn of `Info` logging within [dns.go](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/dns/dns.go#L583). Neither the `--v` flag, nor the `--stderrthreshold=2` flags appear to have any impact. On a 65 node cluster with approximately 1700 pods, this results in a log load of over 10,000 log entries per second. Can we implement a mechanism to turn off Info-level logging from kubedns?\n\nSee also CoreOS kubernetes issue [555](https://github.com/coreos/coreos-kubernetes/pull/555#issuecomment-229530165).\n",
